====================================================
SECTION 1 — PROJECT CONTEXT (Give this to AI first)
====================================================

"I am building a web-based management platform for a social
media marketing and content creation agency called Sparklenz.
Sparklenz helps businesses grow online through social media
marketing, content creation, and digital management services.

The system must centralize and replace manual spreadsheet-based
operations for 100+ staff and 10,000+ clients.

Tech stack:
- Web-based (browser accessible)
- Secure authentication system
- Robust relational database
- Open-source libraries preferred
- No external payment gateway required

The system has 5 main modules:
1. User & Role Management
2. Client & Package Management
3. Task Management & Staff Scheduling
4. Payment & Revenue Tracking
5. Performance & Analytics Reporting

Non-functional requirements:
- High performance under large user loads
- User-friendly interface
- Data accuracy
- Reliability and uptime
- Scalability
- Always accessible (high availability)"

====================================================
SECTION 2 — DATABASE SCHEMA GENERATION PROMPT
====================================================

Prompt to use:
--------------
"Generate a full relational database schema (SQL) for the
Sparklenz social media agency management system.

Include the following tables with all fields, data types,
primary keys, foreign keys, and constraints:

1. users
   - id (UUID, PK)
   - name (VARCHAR)
   - email (VARCHAR, UNIQUE)
   - password_hash (VARCHAR)
   - role_id (FK → roles)
   - is_active (BOOLEAN)
   - created_at (TIMESTAMP)

2. roles
   - id (UUID, PK)
   - name (VARCHAR) -- e.g. Admin, Manager, Staff
   - permissions (JSON or TEXT)

3. sessions
   - id (UUID, PK)
   - user_id (FK → users)
   - token (VARCHAR)
   - created_at (TIMESTAMP)
   - expires_at (TIMESTAMP)

4. clients
   - id (UUID, PK)
   - name (VARCHAR)
   - email (VARCHAR)
   - phone (VARCHAR)
   - company (VARCHAR)
   - created_at (TIMESTAMP)

5. packages
   - id (UUID, PK)
   - name (ENUM: Silver, Gold, Platinum, Diamond)
   - description (TEXT)
   - price (DECIMAL)
   - features (JSON)

6. subscriptions
   - id (UUID, PK)
   - client_id (FK → clients)
   - package_id (FK → packages)
   - status (ENUM: Active, Pending, Cancelled)
   - start_date (DATE)
   - end_date (DATE)

7. tasks
   - id (UUID, PK)
   - title (VARCHAR)
   - description (TEXT)
   - client_id (FK → clients)
   - status (ENUM: Pending, In Progress, Completed)
   - deadline (DATE)
   - drive_link (VARCHAR)
   - created_by (FK → users)
   - created_at (TIMESTAMP)

8. task_assignments
   - id (UUID, PK)
   - task_id (FK → tasks)
   - user_id (FK → users)
   - assigned_at (TIMESTAMP)

9. payments
   - id (UUID, PK)
   - client_id (FK → clients)
   - amount (DECIMAL)
   - payment_date (DATE)
   - note (TEXT)
   - recorded_by (FK → users)
   - created_at (TIMESTAMP)

10. performance_metrics
    - id (UUID, PK)
    - client_id (FK → clients)
    - month (DATE)
    - reach (BIGINT)
    - impressions (BIGINT)
    - engagement (DECIMAL) -- percentage
    - recorded_by (FK → users)
    - created_at (TIMESTAMP)

Generate this as PostgreSQL-compatible SQL with all
constraints, indexes on foreign keys, and timestamps."

====================================================
SECTION 3 — BACKEND API GENERATION PROMPT
====================================================

Prompt to use:
--------------
"Generate a RESTful API using Node.js + Express (or Laravel PHP)
for the Sparklenz agency management system.

Implement the following endpoints:

--- AUTH ---
POST   /api/auth/register       -- Register new user
POST   /api/auth/login          -- Login, return JWT
POST   /api/auth/logout         -- Invalidate token
GET    /api/auth/me             -- Get current user

--- USERS & ROLES ---
GET    /api/users               -- List all users (Admin only)
GET    /api/users/:id           -- Get user by ID
PUT    /api/users/:id           -- Update user profile
DELETE /api/users/:id           -- Deactivate user
GET    /api/roles               -- List roles
POST   /api/roles               -- Create role
PUT    /api/roles/:id           -- Update role/permissions
DELETE /api/roles/:id           -- Delete role

--- CLIENTS ---
POST   /api/clients             -- Add client
GET    /api/clients             -- List all clients
GET    /api/clients/:id         -- Get client detail
PUT    /api/clients/:id         -- Update client
DELETE /api/clients/:id         -- Remove client

--- PACKAGES & SUBSCRIPTIONS ---
POST   /api/packages            -- Create package
GET    /api/packages            -- List packages
PUT    /api/packages/:id        -- Edit package
DELETE /api/packages/:id        -- Delete package
POST   /api/subscriptions       -- Assign package to client
GET    /api/subscriptions/:clientId -- Get client subscription
PUT    /api/subscriptions/:id   -- Renew or change
DELETE /api/subscriptions/:id   -- Cancel subscription

--- TASKS ---
POST   /api/tasks               -- Create task
GET    /api/tasks               -- List tasks (filter by client/status)
GET    /api/tasks/:id           -- Get task detail
PUT    /api/tasks/:id           -- Update task (status, deadline, link)
DELETE /api/tasks/:id           -- Delete task
POST   /api/tasks/:id/assign    -- Assign member to task
DELETE /api/tasks/:id/assign/:userId -- Unassign member

--- PAYMENTS ---
POST   /api/payments            -- Log payment
GET    /api/payments            -- List payments
GET    /api/payments/:id        -- Get payment detail
PUT    /api/payments/:id        -- Edit payment record
DELETE /api/payments/:id        -- Void payment record
GET    /api/clients/:id/balance -- View client balance
GET    /api/reports/revenue     -- Revenue report (monthly)

--- PERFORMANCE ---
POST   /api/metrics             -- Log metrics
GET    /api/metrics             -- List metrics (filter by client/month)
PUT    /api/metrics/:id         -- Update metric entry
DELETE /api/metrics/:id         -- Remove metric entry
GET    /api/reports/performance/:clientId -- Monthly performance report

Use JWT middleware for protected routes. Apply role-based
access control (Admin, Manager, Staff). Return consistent
JSON responses with status codes. Include input validation."

